00:52:26,146 --> 00:52:29,691
We aren't but a few miles from Mexico.
Why is that?

515
00:52:29,900 --> 00:52:32,861
Perhaps they're scared.

516
00:52:32,945 --> 00:52:35,322
Why would they be scared?

517
00:52:41,328 --> 00:52:47,167
Because on this side of the river,
they're no longer Mexican.

518
00:52:48,043 --> 00:52:51,630
Not everybody possesses
our sensibilities, David.

519
00:52:56,969 --> 00:53:00,556
There something more you feel the need
to ask me, Sheriff Locke?

520
00:53:06,687 --> 00:53:10,274
I guess it don't matter.
Be leaving soon enough.

521
00:53:11,191 --> 00:53:15,954
Will you?
Didn't find what you were looking for?

522
00:53:16,029 --> 00:53:18,365
As soon as Marisol's fever breaks,
we'll be on our way.

523
00:53:19,032 --> 00:53:21,243
Nowhere particular?

524
00:53:30,127 --> 00:53:32,546
What does that mean?

525
00:53:32,629 --> 00:53:35,715
"I'll embrace your company
while I have it."

526
00:54:29,853 --> 00:54:32,356
How long have I been asleep?

527
00:54:36,109 --> 00:54:38,945
Most of yesterday and today.

528
00:54:41,448 --> 00:54:43,450
I saw you in the river.

529
00:54:55,003 --> 00:54:57,047
It's the fever.

530
00:54:57,130 --> 00:55:00,467
- It's made you delirious.
- You're not listening to me.

531
00:55:00,551 --> 00:55:02,386
There's something twisting in me.

532
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:06,056
Morris says just a few days.

533
00:55:06,139 --> 00:55:08,558
- Why are you not listening?
- Because you're not thinking straight.

534
00:55:08,642 --> 00:55:12,980
No! I see it all so clear.

535
00:55:13,063 --> 00:55:17,859
You just took me when he gave me away.

536
00:55:17,943 --> 00:55:20,696
You never asked.

537
00:55:21,363 --> 00:55:24,241
You think I'm crazy,
but I had no say in it.

538
00:55:24,324 --> 00:55:26,451
All I think is that right now
you're not yourself.

539
00:55:26,535 --> 00:55:28,454
You're very ill.

540
00:55:31,540 --> 00:55:35,502
I need to see Abraham.
Can you send for him, please?

541
00:55:35,586 --> 00:55:37,129
- No.
- Please.

542
00:55:37,212 --> 00:55:39,131
He's the only one that can help us, David.

543
00:55:39,214 --> 00:55:41,967
God damn it. Help with what? How?

544
00:55:42,050 --> 00:55:45,136
You don't know Abraham. You know me.

545
00:55:45,220 --> 00:55:47,889
And I'm right here. I can help you.

546
00:55:47,973 --> 00:55:52,603
He's put you in the river,
like he did to your father.

547
00:55:54,855 --> 00:55:57,107
And you can't hear me.

548
00:56:09,036 --> 00:56:10,829
I'm leaving.

549
00:56:20,297 --> 00:56:22,633
I know you didn't just
stumble into town for no reason.

550
00:56:24,510 --> 00:56:26,971
I can help you,
but you need to come with me.

551
00:56:27,054 --> 00:56:28,597
Help me how? What do you know?

552
00:56:28,680 --> 00:56:30,182
Everyone here knows what happens.

553
00:56:31,099 --> 00:56:34,060
And they will kill you
when you least expect it.

554
00:56:34,144 --> 00:56:35,187
- Just come in and talk...
- No.

555
00:56:35,270 --> 00:56:37,856
Listen, your wife's already gone.

556
00:56:37,940 --> 00:56:39,567
She was gone the moment
you brought her here...

557
00:56:39,650 --> 00:56:40,651
That is enough of that.

558
00:56:40,734 --> 00:56:42,569
Okay? I can protect you. Just talk to me.

559
00:56:42,653 --> 00:56:46,615
I have to go now. Ride to
the first ridge this side of the river.

560
00:56:46,698 --> 00:56:48,491
You'll see what you're looking for there.

561
00:56:48,867 --> 00:56:50,660
I'll meet you at the split-fork crossing.

562
00:56:51,119 --> 00:56:52,454
I'll wait there an hour for you.

563
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:55,332
Naomi, wh... Naomi!

564
00:56:57,042 --> 00:56:58,877
God damn it.

565
00:57:44,673 --> 00:57:46,967
Three miles?

566
00:58:24,838 --> 00:58:26,590
Can you help me, please?

567
00:58:26,673 --> 00:58:29,092
I need to see Abraham.

568
00:58:29,176 --> 00:58:30,427
Abraham!

569
00:58:37,017 --> 00:58:39,853
Abraham, help me.
Something's really wrong.

570
00:58:39,937 --> 00:58:41,814
Where is your husband?

571
00:58:41,897 --> 00:58:44,233
Last I seen, he was
painting his nose down at Hoot's

572
00:58:44,316 --> 00:58:46,610
with that spud-nigger whore Naomi.

573
00:58:58,789 --> 00:59:01,083
Please, I don't know what to do.

574
00:59:02,292 --> 00:59:06,880
Silas, see she gets home and stay by
her side until the sheriff returns.

575
00:59:06,964 --> 00:59:09,758
- Ladies, you fetch Dr. Morris.
- Yes.

576
00:59:11,218 --> 00:59:16,181
If you were mine, Marisol,
I'd not leave your side for anything.

577
00:59:33,073 --> 00:59:37,586
Why, I recall, at Bull Run,

578
00:59:37,661 --> 00:59:40,414
I led my militia through a wall

579
00:59:40,497 --> 00:59:45,377
of advancing blue-belly
fire entirely unscathed.

580
00:59:45,460 --> 00:59:48,171
"How so?" one might ask.

581
00:59:50,549 --> 00:59:55,387
But, friends, this is
divine conviction at work.

582
00:59:55,470 --> 01:00:00,100
I tell you,
we left even General Lee speechless.

583
01:00:01,184 --> 01:00:03,354
You met General Lee?

584
01:00:03,437 --> 01:00:09,193
Oh, it was a magnificent day to behold.

585
01:00:09,276 --> 01:00:12,746
My men killed more Yankee malefactor

586
01:00:12,821 --> 01:00:18,118
than that milksop
Bedford Forrest's entire regiment.

587
01:00:19,036 --> 01:00:22,998
I believe he referred to us
as his "Hangman Militia."

588
01:00:31,507 --> 01:00:34,593
Did you kill many men, Abraham?

589
01:00:39,264 --> 01:00:42,517
The faces of those we've killed

590
01:00:43,060 --> 01:00:48,482
remains hidden behind our eyes

591
01:00:48,565 --> 01:00:52,027
and our memory for eternity,

592
01:00:52,694 --> 01:00:54,905
without change.

593
01:00:58,116 --> 01:01:01,161
There's no labor in killing a man.

594
01:01:01,245 --> 01:01:04,290
But for some,
it's living after that's work.

595
01:01:05,999 --> 01:01:09,461
You carry the burden of many.

596
01:01:09,586 --> 01:01:12,172
So should you.

597
01:01:12,506 --> 01:01:15,551
Mrs. Naomi Ellis, for one.

598
01:01:23,308 --> 01:01:29,356
My reflection is murderous,
but my conscience is clean.

599
01:01:30,816 --> 01:01:33,152
Your wife...

600
01:01:44,913 --> 01:01:47,165
- No, st... shh.
- Ah!

601
01:01:47,249 --> 01:01:50,419
It's okay, it's okay. I'm here.
Calm down, calm down.

602
01:01:50,794 --> 01:01:53,505
I'm here. I'm here.

603
01:02:24,286 --> 01:02:26,079
David?

604
01:02:28,874 --> 01:02:30,793
You're leaving me again.

605
01:02:35,797 --> 01:02:38,550
I saw something yesterday, Marisol.

606
01:02:51,563 --> 01:02:54,066
We're leaving tonight.

607
01:02:55,484 --> 01:02:57,569
I'll be back before dark.

608
01:03:38,694 --> 01:03:42,656
Gentlemen... pick your prey.

609
01:04:06,889 --> 01:04:09,183
That one.

610
01:04:09,266 --> 01:04:10,726
The woman?

611
01:04:10,809 --> 01:04:12,436
You are twisted, brother.

612
01:04:14,438 --> 01:04:15,898
There you are.

613
01:04:22,487 --> 01:04:23,989
The boy.

614
01:04:50,891 --> 01:04:54,395
Gentlemen, make your preparations.

615
01:07:12,115 --> 01:07:15,535
Don't look like abuelito
is going to give you much of a hunt.

616
01:07:18,330 --> 01:07:20,541
Just the same.

617
01:07:55,450 --> 01:07:57,160
Ah!

618
01:08:05,961 --> 01:08:09,131
Go ahead, give her another one.

619
01:08:33,113 --> 01:08:34,740
Good job, son.

620
01:08:45,751 --> 01:08:48,087
You gotta take the scalp, George.

621
01:08:48,754 --> 01:08:51,757
Nothing to it, quick slit and a pull.

622
01:08:54,510 --> 01:08:56,429
I guarantee you, she'd take yours.

623
01:08:57,221 --> 01:08:59,515
They're as wild as injuns.

624
01:09:30,921 --> 01:09:32,882
Whoo-hoo!

625
01:09:35,300 --> 01:09:37,177
Whoo!

626
01:09:44,268 --> 01:09:46,020
You bury her good, now, Isaac.

627
01:09:46,270 --> 01:09:47,855
I will.

628
01:11:26,078 --> 01:11:27,329
...the sins...

629
01:11:36,046 --> 01:11:37,464
Marisol?

630
01:11:39,550 --> 01:11:41,135
Marisol?

631
01:11:41,218 --> 01:11:42,511
Move, get out of the way! Move!

632
01:11:45,514 --> 01:11:46,974
The hell are you doing to my wife?!

633
01:11:48,100 --> 01:11:51,895
She's no longer yours, David.

634
01:11:51,979 --> 01:11:54,356
Take him.

635
01:12:01,572 --> 01:12:03,532
Let God in you.

636
01:12:12,916 --> 01:12:14,584
Keys.

637
01:12:21,925 --> 01:12:23,093
Get up.

638
01:12:35,022 --> 01:12:37,441
Open this door.

639
01:12:41,361 --> 01:12:43,697
I missed the first five shots.

640
01:12:43,780 --> 01:12:46,783
I mean, I must have picked the quickest
Mexican out of the whole bloody bunch.

641
01:12:46,867 --> 01:12:48,077
Mine damn near got to the river!

642
01:12:48,160 --> 01:12:51,872
Monte said that's the farthest
any Mexican ever made it!

643
01:12:51,955 --> 01:12:55,125
God damn it, that was a hell of a time.

644
01:12:59,838 --> 01:13:01,673
What do you figure on doing with that?

645
01:13:11,934 --> 01:13:14,770
You two put your fucking guns down slowly.

646
01:13:21,360 --> 01:13:23,195
Everyone sit up.

647
01:13:23,278 --> 01:13:26,490
You and you, take everyone's pistols
and put them over there.

648
01:13:37,751 --> 01:13:39,586
You killed my son.

649
01:13:42,548 --> 01:13:44,759
I hear your wife's sick.

650
01:13:56,770 --> 01:13:58,188
What are you going to do?

651
01:13:59,898 --> 01:14:02,734
I'm going to sit and wait.

652
01:14:05,362 --> 01:14:07,573
You paid good money to come here, right?

653
01:14:10,200 --> 01:14:12,577
How much were those Mexicans worth?

654
01:14:18,458 --> 01:14:20,710
How much?

655
01:14:20,794 --> 01:14:24,756
Two hundred a hunt. $200 per hunt!

656
01:14:25,465 --> 01:14:27,759
And that's what you call it?

657
01:14:27,843 --> 01:14:29,303
Hunting?

658
01:14:29,386 --> 01:14:31,889
No, please.

659
01:14:34,349 --> 01:14:36,685
Why are you here, old man?

660
01:14:39,146 --> 01:14:41,190
Because we wanted to kill something.

661
01:14:41,273 --> 01:14:44,151
Something or someone?

662
01:14:44,234 --> 01:14:46,278
Someone.

663
01:14:46,361 --> 01:14:50,699
We wanted to know
what it felt like to kill someone.

664
01:14:52,659 --> 01:14:54,494
Well, I'm gonna let you kill.

665
01:14:55,579 --> 01:14:57,998
And I ain't even gonna charge you for it.

666
01:15:09,510 --> 01:15:11,721
You're gonna pick up that pistol

667
01:15:12,346 --> 01:15:15,933
and shoot Monte
in his ugly fucking face...

668
01:15:18,268 --> 01:15:20,270
or I'm gonna shoot your father dead.

669
01:15:24,900 --> 01:15:28,570
In fact, go on and shoot Dale, too.
I don't much like his face either.

670
01:15:33,242 --> 01:15:35,202
Pick up the pistol, killer.

671
01:15:39,498 --> 01:15:41,542
Pick it up!

672
01:15:54,429 --> 01:15:56,348
Don't do it, John.

673
01:15:56,431 --> 01:15:58,183
Come on, son.

674
01:15:58,267 --> 01:16:01,061
Come on, he...
he's fooling with you, John.

675
01:16:03,647 --> 01:16:06,024
- Please.
- One!

676
01:16:45,147 --> 01:16:47,983
You say one word
and I'll blow your fucking head off.

677
01:17:01,038 --> 01:17:02,998
Where is my wife?

678
01:17:07,920 --> 01:17:10,339
Where she belongs.

679
01:17:14,676 --> 01:17:18,096
You can go right ahead and put that
old coach gun down now, mister.

680
01:17:18,805 --> 01:17:21,516
Aw, I figure I won't.

681
01:17:21,600 --> 01:17:23,986
It's all right, boys.

682
01:17:24,061 --> 01:17:28,399
I feel Mr. Kingston is due
a modicum of self-expression

683
01:17:28,482 --> 01:17:30,818
under the circumstances.

684
01:17:31,693 --> 01:17:33,570
Kingston?

685
01:17:33,987 --> 01:17:38,366
I've known for quite some time
you'd be coming for me, David.

686
01:17:38,450 --> 01:17:42,871
I took pleasure in killing your father.

687
01:17:42,955 --> 01:17:46,041
He was an abhorrent man.

688
01:17:47,918 --> 01:17:50,295
If you think I'm here to avenge my father,

689
01:17:50,379 --> 01:17:52,298
you think too highly of yourself.

690
01:17:53,048 --> 01:17:56,760
You're nothing more to me
than youthful intrigue.

691
01:17:58,095 --> 01:18:01,223
I'm a Texas Ranger.
I was sent by the governor himself.

692
01:18:01,306 --> 01:18:03,558
All those Mexicans you've been killing

693
01:18:03,642 --> 01:18:06,353
been floating into a strainer
a couple miles downriver.

694
01:18:06,436 --> 01:18:09,439
One was General Calderon's own nephew.

695
01:18:16,822 --> 01:18:19,325
Well, I must say

696
01:18:19,408 --> 01:18:23,704
all this news is shocking, David.

697
01:18:26,790 --> 01:18:29,376
Though it seems you have
some bad information.

698
01:18:29,459 --> 01:18:31,836
You see, we bury the bodies.

699
01:18:31,920 --> 01:18:36,049
Mexicans, shit that they are,

700
01:18:36,133 --> 01:18:39,186
decompose rather quickly.

701
01:18:39,261 --> 01:18:42,681
How dirty did you get
that shovel today, Isaac?

702
01:18:47,352 --> 01:18:49,905
Don't listen to him, Father.
You're a fucking liar.

703
01:18:49,980 --> 01:18:52,232
I followed you today, you piece of shit.

704
01:18:52,316 --> 01:18:54,785
How long you think before
they find that scalpless girl

705
01:18:54,860 --> 01:18:56,195
you dumped in the river?

706
01:18:58,155 --> 01:19:00,366
Father, I... I can explain.

707
01:19:00,449 --> 01:19:03,627
Father, can't you...
can't you see what he's doing?

708
01:19:03,702 --> 01:19:05,996
I tell you, he's... he's lying.

709
01:19:06,079 --> 01:19:09,916
You are as crippled as your mother was.

710
01:19:21,929 --> 01:19:26,600
I suppose I'll have to
try again with the new wife.

711
01:19:26,683 --> 01:19:30,061
I'll shoot you dead before
you ever touch her again.

712
01:19:30,187 --> 01:19:34,867
I have to say, as much as
I respect your confidence, David,

713
01:19:34,942 --> 01:19:38,112
I also respect when a man can appreciate

714
01:19:38,195 --> 01:19:40,572
his fate staring him in the face.

715
01:19:40,656 --> 01:19:44,410
You have Hoot's rifle
pointing at your head, son.

716
01:19:44,493 --> 01:19:47,538
I figure I'm a better shot than Hoot.

717
01:20:06,849 --> 01:20:10,144
Your pugnacious pappy
would have loved to hear that.

718
01:20:10,227 --> 01:20:12,896
- Abraham?
- I say he's bluffing.

719
01:20:12,980 --> 01:20:15,774
- Father, may I have a moment?
- No!

720
01:20:24,950 --> 01:20:26,493
David Kingston...

721
01:20:29,454 --> 01:20:36,461
I challenge you to fight me
to the death in a Helena duel.

722
01:20:43,719 --> 01:20:45,721
My boy.

723
01:20:47,347 --> 01:20:49,724
Let me do this, Father.

724
01:20:58,192 --> 01:21:00,403
Let me help you up, son.

725
01:21:04,114 --> 01:21:05,824
David?

726
01:21:09,119 --> 01:21:11,079
I'll do it on one condition.

727
01:21:12,748 --> 01:21:16,001
When it's done,
my wife leaves here with me.

728
01:21:18,962 --> 01:21:23,383
Put your guns away, gentlemen.
There'll be no more shooting today.

729
01:21:36,104 --> 01:21:39,274
We'll meet outside, 8:00.

730
01:21:52,704 --> 01:21:54,414
Good people of Mount Hermon,

731
01:21:56,500 --> 01:22:00,337
you're about to witness a Helena duel.

732
01:22:01,964 --> 01:22:03,632
Mr. Kingston.

733
01:22:08,804 --> 01:22:13,726
A most noble affair
of character and honor.

734
01:22:16,019 --> 01:22:23,068
I took David's father with this knife
over 20 years ago.

735
01:22:23,902 --> 01:22:26,822
The one he now grips
is stained with my blood

736
01:22:26,905 --> 01:22:29,074
from that same duel

737
01:22:29,575 --> 01:22:34,246
and now will surely drip red
with my son's.

738
01:22:37,833 --> 01:22:44,631
If Isaac lives, he will be forgiven
his ill-considered behavior

739
01:22:44,715 --> 01:22:47,226
and he will undoubtedly be the better man

740
01:22:47,301 --> 01:22:49,762
for what he experiences here tonight.

741
01:22:52,389 --> 01:22:54,433
Does me proud.

742
01:22:57,686 --> 01:23:03,734
If David is victor, then in fairness,
he will be taken to his wife

743
01:23:03,817 --> 01:23:06,278
and she will decide their fate.

744
01:23:06,820 --> 01:23:10,574
On this, you have my word.
Gentlemen, come together.

745
01:23:17,497 --> 01:23:21,042
You shall pour out each other's blood...

746
01:23:22,002 --> 01:23:24,671
and we will cover it with dust.

747
01:23:41,605 --> 01:23:42,606
Begin.

748
01:24:55,971 --> 01:24:57,681
- Marisol?
- Shh.

749
01:25:00,309 --> 01:25:04,230
You'll pull your stitches out
and bleed everywhere.

750
01:25:07,482 --> 01:25:09,317
We can go home now.

751
01:25:25,501 --> 01:25:29,596
"Dark eyes burning,
in the night they glow.

752
01:25:29,671 --> 01:25:34,843
She knows only yearning.
What else is there to know?"

753
01:25:35,636 --> 01:25:38,180
That's beautiful, David.

754
01:25:40,432 --> 01:25:42,726
And that's a lovely drawing.

755
01:25:43,602 --> 01:25:46,355
You are one surprise after another.

756
01:25:51,235 --> 01:25:54,113
You've been busy when no one was watching.

757
01:25:57,115 --> 01:25:59,951
Thank you for sharing, Marisol.

758
01:26:01,203 --> 01:26:03,414
He wanted us to escape.

759
01:26:03,497 --> 01:26:04,999
Did he, now?

760
01:26:06,041 --> 01:26:11,880
Well, we're going to give you
that chance, David.

761
01:26:11,964 --> 01:26:14,758
These three men have yet to experience

762
01:26:14,842 --> 01:26:16,969
the thrill of the hunt.

763
01:26:17,052 --> 01:26:22,391
I've decided to afford them
this one unique opportunity.

764
01:26:22,474 --> 01:26:24,351
Obviously, you're disadvantaged,

765
01:26:24,434 --> 01:26:26,728
so we'll give you
till first light tomorrow.

766
01:26:26,812 --> 01:26:28,772
The time until then is yours.

767
01:26:28,856 --> 01:26:32,735
I've given you a rifle
and a generous amount of shells.

768
01:26:33,986 --> 01:26:35,321
Gentlemen?

769
01:26:46,790 --> 01:26:49,084
Please get him dressed and fed.

770
01:27:04,183 --> 01:27:06,560
Please put this on.

771
01:27:08,061 --> 01:27:10,605
Marisol?

772
01:27:10,689 --> 01:27:12,733
Why are you doing this?

773
01:27:22,284 --> 01:27:23,952
Marisol?

774
01:31:24,776 --> 01:31:26,861
You are not from the town.

775
01:31:28,989 --> 01:31:31,783
What is your name?

776
01:31:31,867 --> 01:31:33,452
David Kingston.

777
01:31:35,078 --> 01:31:36,580
I'm a Ranger.

778
01:31:39,458 --> 01:31:41,585
I am Maria.

779
01:31:43,962 --> 01:31:46,381
Maria Calderon.

780
01:31:49,259 --> 01:31:51,511
Your uncle's looking for you.

781
01:32:03,524 --> 01:32:05,276
Thank you.

782
01:32:14,409 --> 01:32:16,786
Best get on now, Miss Calderon.

783
01:32:26,046 --> 01:32:28,382
How do you know he would've come this way?

784
01:32:29,591 --> 01:32:32,969
I've known where this boy's
been headed his entire life.

785
01:32:33,053 --> 01:32:35,138
He was wounded
something fierce from the fight.

786
01:32:35,222 --> 01:32:36,849
Probably dead anyway.

787
01:32:37,391 --> 01:32:40,311
I assure you, gentlemen, he is not.

788
01:32:41,478 --> 01:32:43,814
Whoa, whoa.

789
01:33:00,914 --> 01:33:02,598
Shit! Shit!

790
01:33:02,666 --> 01:33:04,751
He ain't dead! God damn it!

791
01:33:04,835 --> 01:33:07,046
- God damn it!
- Get your head down!

792
01:33:09,631 --> 01:33:11,424
- I knew it, I knew it.
- Shit!

793
01:33:11,592 --> 01:33:13,177
Son of a bitch.

794
01:33:16,388 --> 01:33:18,181
What are we going to do, Abraham?

795
01:33:22,311 --> 01:33:23,604
Shit! There goes the horses.

796
01:33:23,687 --> 01:33:25,948
We gotta go back. We can't stay here.

797
01:33:26,023 --> 01:33:28,317
Please, I... I can't fight.

798
01:33:28,483 --> 01:33:29,943
I can't... I...

799
01:37:13,500 --> 01:37:15,419
Ah, fuck.

800
01:38:37,459 --> 01:38:39,670
I'm guessing you didn't foresee this.

801
01:39:00,816 --> 01:39:06,155
You should thank me
for taking your father.

802
01:39:06,238 --> 01:39:08,907
You were born that day.

803
01:39:10,534 --> 01:39:14,204
If he raised you, you would
not be the man you've become.

804
01:39:15,706 --> 01:39:21,629
Our entire lives
spent denying death its dominion.

805
01:39:21,712 --> 01:39:24,089
Seems its answer for us will be...

806
01:39:24,173 --> 01:39:26,759
painful and slow.

807
01:39:28,510 --> 01:39:30,429
We deserve it for all we've done.

808
01:39:32,431 --> 01:39:36,060
Futile to toil over such things.

809
01:39:36,685 --> 01:39:39,396
Forces you to look inward

810
01:39:39,479 --> 01:39:43,942
and examine the monster you truly are.

811
01:39:45,986 --> 01:39:48,197
Don't go exempting yourself.

812
01:39:49,031 --> 01:39:52,117
You'll answer the same as everyone else.

813
01:39:52,201 --> 01:39:58,207
David, I was never born
nor will I ever truly die.

814
01:39:59,833 --> 01:40:02,336
Aw, you'll die, all right.

815
01:40:02,419 --> 01:40:04,755
You'll die right here.

816
01:40:06,215 --> 01:40:08,634
Your leg will swell.

817
01:40:08,717 --> 01:40:12,221
You'll scream and try to
kill yourself to save the pain.

818
01:40:12,429 --> 01:40:14,681
The stench will lead them
to our bodies in a week

819
01:40:14,765 --> 01:40:16,809
and this scene will show
what I have made of you.

820
01:40:18,560 --> 01:40:21,563
Word will spread of your death.

821
01:40:21,647 --> 01:40:26,152
They'll hiss your name, call you
a murderous son of a bitch and a fraud.

822
01:40:31,740 --> 01:40:37,621
The only thing
they'll remember of you will be me.

823
01:42:30,275 --> 01:42:32,444
Get him! Get him!

824
01:42:35,113 --> 01:42:36,406
Yes!

825
01:43:03,267 --> 01:43:04,935
I made you.

826
01:43:06,353 --> 01:43:09,105
And so I end you.

827
01:43:50,814 --> 01:43:53,400
You did send your Rangers out to the town

828
01:43:53,483 --> 01:43:57,321
to corroborate the stories that my niece
gave you along with the prisoners?

829
01:43:57,404 --> 01:44:00,032
The... the town was abandoned.

830
01:44:00,115 --> 01:44:01,992
And the prison?

831
01:44:02,075 --> 01:44:04,828
It doesn't appear to exist.

832
01:44:08,540 --> 01:44:13,587
Did your niece say anything else
regarding David Kingston or his wife?

833
01:44:15,672 --> 01:44:18,475
She said he was badly wounded
when he freed the prisoners

834
01:44:18,550 --> 01:44:23,096
and he rode out into the brush alone,

835
01:44:23,180 --> 01:44:25,724
never to be seen again.

836
01:44:25,807 --> 01:44:27,976
But she made no mention of a woman.

837
01:44:29,811 --> 01:44:33,565
Perhaps you will allow me a small detail
to go out and search for him.

838
01:44:33,649 --> 01:44:38,654
I don't think so, General.
He rode off into the brush for a reason.

839
01:44:40,531 --> 01:44:44,118
If he wants to, he'll ride back out again.

